  The screener only shows a stock if ALL 4 rules pass:

  RULE 1 — Uptrend filter
    Close >= 50-day MA × {MA_FILTER}
    Why: We only want breakouts in rising stocks

  RULE 2 — Swing high detection
    Local maximum with {LOOKBACK} candles on each side
    Why: Identifies actual pivot highs, not noise

  RULE 3 — Resistance validation  ← THE KEY RULE
    After the swing high, price must drop >= {MIN_PULLBACK_PCT}%
    Why: Proves the level was REJECTED by the market
         Without this, BHEL's current rally peak falsely
         appears as a "resistance to break"

  RULE 4 — Pre-breakout proximity
    Price must be within {THRESHOLD_PCT}% below the resistance
    Why: You want to enter BEFORE the breakout, not after

BACKTEST LOGIC:
  For each signal, we simulate a trade:
    Entry : when close breaks above resistance
    Target: +{SUCCESS_TARGET_PCT}% above resistance level
    Stop  : -{STOP_LOSS_PCT}% below resistance level
    Max hold: {MAX_HOLD_CANDLES} trading days
""")

    # ── Part 1: Explain current state for key stocks ──────────
    print("\n" + "═"*65)
    print("  PART 1: WHY DOES/DOESN'T THE SCREENER SHOW EACH STOCK?")
    print("═"*65)
    for sym in TEST_SYMBOLS:
        explain_current_state(sym)

    # ── Part 2: Full backtest ─────────────────────────────────
    print("\n\n" + "═"*65)
    print("  PART 2: FULL BACKTEST (2 YEARS WALK-FORWARD)")
    print("═"*65)
    summary = []
    for sym in TEST_SYMBOLS:
        result = backtest_symbol(sym, verbose=True)
        if result:
            summary.append(result)

    # ── Overall summary ───────────────────────────────────────
    if summary:
        print("\n" + "█"*65)
        print("  OVERALL BACKTEST SUMMARY")
        print("█"*65)
        total_wins   = sum(s["wins"]    for s in summary)
        total_losses = sum(s["losses"]  for s in summary)
        total_sigs   = sum(s["signals"] for s in summary)
        overall_wr   = round(total_wins / (total_wins + total_losses) * 100, 1) \
                       if (total_wins + total_losses) > 0 else 0

        rows = [[s["symbol"].replace(".NS",""), s["signals"],
                 s["wins"], s["losses"], s["pending"],
                 f"{s['win_rate']}%"] for s in summary]
        print(tabulate(rows,
              headers=["Stock","Signals","Wins","Losses","Open","Win Rate"],
              tablefmt="rounded_outline"))
        print(f"\n  Combined win rate : {overall_wr}%  ({total_wins}W / {total_losses}L)")
        print(f"  Total signals     : {total_sigs} across {len(summary)} stocks / 2 years")
        print()
